parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Instrument Cluster Failure (Speedometer and Fuel Gauge)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can lead to inaccurate speed readings, which can cause accidents, and incorrect fuel level readings, which can lead to unexpected engine stalling, stranding the driver, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The speedometer needle pegs or reads incorrectly
the speedometer shows inconsistent or erratic readings
the fuel gauge reads incorrectly or shows empty when the tank is not empty
the instrument cluster displays faulty or inconsistent readings.
